column1: Producer (person or business who creates the waste) details
column22: Receiver (person or business who receives the waste for recovery or disposal) details
column50: Second waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a second EWC code)
column65: Third waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a third EWC code)
column80: Fourth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a fourth EWC code)
column95: Fifth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a fifth EWC code)
column110: Sixth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a sixth EWC code)
column125: Seventh waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a seventh EWC code)
column140: Eighth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a eighth EWC code)
column155: Ninth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a ninth EWC code)
column170: Tenth waste type details if required (all waste details are compulsory if you enter a tenth EWC code)

column1: Your unique reference (maximum 20 characters, letters and numbers only)
column12: Waste collection address Line 1 (only enter if different to producer address)
column16: Waste collection postcode (only enter if different to producer address)
column17: Waste source (household, commercial, industrial, local authority, or demolition)
column18: Broker registration number (only enter if applicable)
column19: Carrier registration number (starts with CBD, then either U or L, followed by 4 to 6 numbers)
column20: Mode of waste transport (road, rail, air, sea, or inland waterway)
column21: Expected waste collection date (only use numbers and slashes between the day, month and year, for example 13/01/25)
column22: Receiver  authorisation type (permit, licence, regulatory position statement, or other local agreement)
column23: Receiver  environmental permit number or waste exepmtion number (if applicable)
column33: Number and type of transportation containers (max 250 characters)
column34: Special handling requirements details (only enter if applicable, max 250 characters)
column35: EWC code (six digits, only use numbers)
column37: Physical form of waste (gas, liquid, solid, powder, sludge, or mixed)
column38: Waste quantity (numbers and decimal points only)
column39: Quantity units (tonnes, kilograms, litres, or cubic metres)
column41: Chemical and biological components of the waste (separate multiple components using a semi colon. For example, textured coatings; floor tiles)
column42: Chemical or biological concentrations value (separate multiple amounts using a semi colon)
column43: Chemical or biological concentrations unit of measure (% or mg/kg, separate multiple amounts using a semi colon)

column45: Enter all hazardous waste codes (if applicable)

column47: Enter persistent organic pollutants (POPs) details (if applicable)
column48: Enter POPs concentration value, using only numbers and a full stop
column49: Enter POPs concentration unit of measure, for example %
